  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Euclid"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Rendering Meshes"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "After creating some 3D shapes, you probably want to actually ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "display",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " them.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Most of the Euclid library is completely self-contained, with no dependencies on any particular rendering technology or framework.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "However, when running on iOS or macOS you can take advantage of Euclid’s built-in SceneKit integration.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This is demonstrated in the Example app included with the project.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "SceneKit is Apple’s high-level 3D engine, which can use either OpenGL or Metal for rendering on supported devices.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Euclid provides extensions for creating an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNGeometry",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " from a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", as well as converting Euclid ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Vector",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Rotation",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " types to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNVector",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNQuaternion",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " respectively.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The SceneKit integration makes it easy to display Euclid geometry on-screen, and to integrate with ARKit, etc.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can also use SceneKit to export Euclid-generated ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in standard 3D model formats such as DAE, STL or OBJ.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Materials",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Materials",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Interesting geometry is one thing, but to really bring a shape to life it needs colors and textures.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Every ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Polygon",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " has a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Polygon\/material-swift.property",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " property that can be used to apply any kind of material you like on a per-polygon basis.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "All primitives and builder methods accept a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "material",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameter which will apply that material to every polygon in the resultant ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "When you later combine meshes using CSG operations, the original materials from the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " that contributed to each part of the resultant shape are preserved.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Before a material can be used with SceneKit, you need to convert the Euclid material to an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If the material is already an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instance it will be used directly.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If the material is a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Color",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UI\/NSColor",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UI\/NSImage",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " it will be converted to an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " automatically.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For all other material types, you will need to do this conversion yourself.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can convert materials using the optional closure argument for Euclid’s ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNGeometry",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " constructor, which receives the Euclid material as an input and returns an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When serializing Euclid geometry using ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Codable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", only specific material types can be supported.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Currently, material serialization works for ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "String",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "s, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Int",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "s, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Color",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and any class that conforms to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "NSCoding",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " (which includes many UIKit, AppKit and SceneKit types, such as ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UI\/NSColor",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UI\/NSImage",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ").",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Colors",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Colors",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Euclid currently has no support for setting colors on a per-vertex basis, but you can apply colors to a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Polygon",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " using the material property.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The material property is of type ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "AnyHashable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " which basically means it can be anything you want.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can set the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "material",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to an instance of Euclid’s ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Color",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", or you can use a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UIColor",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "NSColor",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instead if you prefer.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This approach is demonstrated in the Example app included in the project.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Textures",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Textures",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Euclid automatically adds 2D texture coordinates to the vertices of a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " created using primitives or builder methods.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "There is limited control over how those coordinates are specified at the moment, but they allow for simple spherical and cylindrical texture wrapping.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To apply a texture image to a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", store a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "UIImage",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "NSImage",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " as the material property and it will be converted to an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " automatically.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you want to do something more complex, such as applying both a color ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "and",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " texture to the same ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/com.charcoaldesign.Euclid\/documentation\/Euclid\/Mesh",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", or maybe including a normal map or some other material properties, you could create a custom material type to store all the properties you care about, or even assign an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "SCNMaterial",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " directly as the material for your Euclid geometry.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
